Condition : 35 - Prior to commencement of the development a Biodiversity Enhancement Strategy, in line with the submitted Preliminary Ecological Appraisal, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The Biodiversity Enhancement Strategy shall incorporate, where relevant:
-	Tree removal strategy;
-	Installation of sensitive/low UV lighting;
-	Protection of existing mature trees and shrubs;
-	Replacement vegetation with naturalistic/wildlife planting
-	Increased amount of vegetation on the site against the current baseline with native/wildlife planting;
-	Installation of a green wall/climbers or a biodiverse roof;
-	Installation of bird and bat boxes;
-	Good horticultural practice; and
-	Details of how the enhancement measures will be monitored, managed and maintained as such.
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and retained thereafter.
